
At Coll. Carys [Ampthill, Chesterfield co.], 13 Feb. 1781. Was at Manchester last night, but too late to cross the river; is now on his way to see Steuben at Chesterfield Courthouse; will return to Richmond for TJs orders tonight. Mr. Ross intends to set off with me for the Fork of James River the Day after to morrow, if No Contra Orders.
